Note:
SQL Translation Round-Trip Probe

End-to-end proof that the SQL translation pipeline is REAL, not a skeleton:

    SQL source
      -> sql_lexer       (tokenize SELECT/FROM/JOIN/WHERE/GROUP BY/ORDER BY,
                          INSERT/VALUES, UPDATE/SET, DELETE, CREATE TABLE,
                          operators =,<>,<,>,AND/OR, string/number/NULL literals)
      -> sql_parser      (build the SQLNode AST documented atop sql_parser)
      -> sql_to_hir      (lower the AST to the hir.runa dictionary/list HIR)
      -> hir_to_sql      (emit HIR back to valid PostgreSQL text)
      -> re-lex / re-parse / re-lower of the emitted text
      -> structural + CONTENT equality on the key constructs

The SQL HIR node model is hir.runa's dictionary/list literal interchange shared
by sql_to_hir (producer) and hir_to_sql (consumer): a dictionary is a
HIR_DICTIONARY_LITERAL whose entries List (16-byte [key, value] blocks) hangs at
the children slot; a list is a HIR_ARRAY_LITERAL whose elements List hangs at the
children slot; string payloads are HIR string-literal nodes read with
get_string_literal_value. Identifiers lower to {type: identifier, name}; string
literals stay as bare HIR string literals. This probe reads HIR through exactly
that contract.

DEPTH: the probe does NOT merely check that nodes exist. It asserts on the
re-parsed HIR2 that the CONTENTS survive: a SELECT's column list (>= 2 columns),
the FROM table name + a JOIN with an ON condition, a WHERE predicate (binary op
with operator and operands), GROUP BY keys, ORDER BY keys; a CREATE TABLE's
column names AND types; an INSERT's value list. A translator that returned an
empty members list (members vanish) makes this probe FAIL.

Exit code: number of failed assertions (0 == all passed). No exit_with_code.
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/sql/sql_to_hir.runa" as SqlFrontend
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/sql/hir_to_sql.runa" as SqlBackend
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir.runa" as HIR
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "tests/test_utils.runa" as TestUtils

Note: ============================================================================
Note: hir.runa dict/list literal decoders (mirror the producer/consumer contract)
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
A SQL HIR dictionary is a HIR_DICTIONARY_LITERAL whose entries List hangs at the
children slot. Each entry is a 16-byte block: key (raw string handle) at offset 0,
value (a child HIR node or HIR string literal) at offset 8. This decoder
linear-scans those entries comparing the raw key with string_equals, returning the
stored value. It is the exact lookup hir_to_sql's get_dictionary_value performs.
@End Reasoning
Process called "dict_get" takes node as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let entries be proc get_dictionary_entries from HIR with node
    If entries is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be proc size from List with entries
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let entry be proc get_at from List with entries, index
        If entry is not equal to 0:
            Let entry_key be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entry, 0
            Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with entry_key, key
            If matches is equal to 1:
                Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entry, 8
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
String fields ("type", "operator", "name", ...) are stored as HIR string literal
nodes. This helper resolves the key then unwraps the literal to its char* payload.
@End Reasoning
Process called "dict_get_string" takes node as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    Let value_node be proc dict_get with node, key
    If value_node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc get_string_literal_value from HIR with value_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
A SQL HIR list is a HIR_ARRAY_LITERAL whose backing element List hangs at the
children slot. Returns the element count (0 when absent).
@End Reasoning
Process called "list_count" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let items be proc get_list_elements from HIR with node
    If items is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc size from List with items
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the element at index in a HIR list node (0 when absent / out of range).
@End Reasoning
Process called "list_at" takes node as Integer, index as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let items be proc get_list_elements from HIR with node
    If items is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc get_at from List with items, index
End Process

@Reasoning:
An identifier HIR node is {type: identifier, name: <string literal>}. This helper
returns the bare name string so the probe can compare column/table names.
@End Reasoning
Process called "identifier_name" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc dict_get_string with node, "name"
End Process

@Reasoning:
Finds the first element of a HIR list whose "type" tag equals the requested kind.
Used to locate the column whose name matches in a CREATE TABLE columns list.
@End Reasoning
Process called "find_column_by_name" takes columns_node as Integer, want_name as Integer returns Integer:
    If columns_node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let items be proc get_list_elements from HIR with columns_node
    If items is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be proc size from List with items
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let col be proc get_at from List with items, index
        Let cname be proc dict_get_string with col, "name"
        If cname is not equal to 0:
            Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with cname, want_name
            If matches is equal to 1:
                Return col
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Pipeline helpers
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Each round of the probe runs the identical front-of-pipeline (lex -> parse ->
lower). translate_sql_to_hir runs all of these as a unit; this wrapper guards
the source so the two runs (original and emitted) are behaviourally identical.
@End Reasoning
Process called "source_to_hir" takes source as Integer returns Integer:
    If source is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc translate_sql_to_hir from SqlFrontend with source, 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Assertion battery applied to a SELECT HIR root
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Runs the full set of SELECT content assertions against one HIR root, so the
identical battery can be applied to HIR1 (original) and HIR2 (round-tripped).
@End Reasoning
Process called "check_select" takes results as Integer, label as Integer, root as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: type == select
    Let root_type be proc dict_get_string with root, "type"
    Let root_type_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with root_type, "select"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, label, root_type_ok, 1

    Note: columns >= 2 and first column survives
    Let columns be proc dict_get with root, "columns"
    Let col_count be proc list_count with columns
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, label, col_count, 2

    Let col0 be proc list_at with columns, 0
    Let col0_name be proc identifier_name with col0
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, label, col0_name

    Note: FROM table name == "users"
    Let from_node be proc dict_get with root, "from"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, label, from_node
    Let from_name be proc identifier_name with from_node
    Let from_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with from_name, "users"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, label, from_ok, 1

    Note: JOIN present with table + ON condition
    Let joins be proc dict_get with root, "joins"
    Let join_count be proc list_count with joins
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, label, join_count, 1
    Let join0 be proc list_at with joins, 0
    Let join_table be proc dict_get with join0, "table"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, label, join_table
    Let join_table_name be proc identifier_name with join_table
    Let join_table_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with join_table_name, "orders"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, label, join_table_ok, 1
    Let join_on be proc dict_get with join0, "on"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, label, join_on
    Let join_on_type be proc dict_get_string with join_on, "type"
    Let join_on_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with join_on_type, "binary_op"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, label, join_on_ok, 1

    Note: WHERE predicate is a binary op with operator + operands
    Let where_node be proc dict_get with root, "where"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, label, where_node
    Let where_type be proc dict_get_string with where_node, "type"
    Let where_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with where_type, "binary_op"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, label, where_ok, 1
    Let where_op be proc dict_get_string with where_node, "operator"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, label, where_op
    Let where_left be proc dict_get with where_node, "left"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, label, where_left
    Let where_right be proc dict_get with where_node, "right"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, label, where_right

    Note: GROUP BY has >= 1 key
    Let group_by be proc dict_get with root, "group_by"
    Let group_count be proc list_count with group_by
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, label, group_count, 1

    Note: ORDER BY has >= 1 key
    Let order_by be proc dict_get with root, "order_by"
    Let order_count be proc list_count with order_by
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, label, order_count, 1

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Runs CREATE TABLE content assertions: table name plus two specific columns with
their datatypes, applied to both HIR1 and HIR2.
@End Reasoning
Process called "check_create" takes results as Integer, label as Integer, root as Integer returns Integer:
    Let root_type be proc dict_get_string with root, "type"
    Let root_type_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with root_type, "create_table"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, label, root_type_ok, 1

    Let table_node be proc dict_get with root, "table"
    Let table_name be proc identifier_name with table_node
    Let table_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with table_name, "accounts"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, label, table_ok, 1

    Let columns be proc dict_get with root, "columns"
    Let col_count be proc list_count with columns
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, label, col_count, 2

    Note: column "id" has a datatype
    Let id_col be proc find_column_by_name with columns, "id"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, label, id_col
    Let id_type be proc dict_get_string with id_col, "datatype"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, label, id_type

    Note: column "name" has a datatype
    Let name_col be proc find_column_by_name with columns, "name"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, label, name_col
    Let name_type be proc dict_get_string with name_col, "datatype"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, label, name_type

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Runs INSERT content assertions: table name, a column list, and a non-empty value
list, applied to both HIR1 and HIR2.
@End Reasoning
Process called "check_insert" takes results as Integer, label as Integer, root as Integer returns Integer:
    Let root_type be proc dict_get_string with root, "type"
    Let root_type_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with root_type, "insert"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, label, root_type_ok, 1

    Let table_node be proc dict_get with root, "table"
    Let table_name be proc identifier_name with table_node
    Let table_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with table_name, "accounts"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, label, table_ok, 1

    Let values be proc dict_get with root, "values"
    Let value_count be proc list_count with values
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, label, value_count, 2

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Probe entry point
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let results be proc create_test_results from TestUtils
    proc begin_suite from TestUtils with results, "SQL translation round-trip"

    Note: ---------------------------------------------------------------------
    Note: SELECT with columns, FROM, INNER JOIN ... ON, WHERE, GROUP BY, ORDER BY
    Note: ---------------------------------------------------------------------
    Let select_src be "SELECT id, name FROM users INNER JOIN orders ON id = id WHERE id > 10 GROUP BY name ORDER BY id"

    Let select_hir1 be proc source_to_hir with select_src
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "SELECT: frontend produced HIR1", select_hir1
    proc check_select with results, "SELECT HIR1 content", select_hir1

    Let select_sql be proc generate_sql_from_hir from SqlBackend with select_hir1
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "SELECT: backend produced SQL text", select_sql
    Let select_sql_len be proc string_length from StringCore with select_sql
    proc assert_greater_than from TestUtils with results, "SELECT: emitted SQL non-empty", select_sql_len, 0

    Let select_hir2 be proc source_to_hir with select_sql
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "SELECT: re-parse produced HIR2", select_hir2
    proc check_select with results, "SELECT HIR2 round-trip content", select_hir2

    Note: ---------------------------------------------------------------------
    Note: CREATE TABLE with column defs + types + constraints
    Note: ---------------------------------------------------------------------
    Let create_src be "CREATE TABLE accounts (id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR NOT NULL, balance NUMERIC)"

    Let create_hir1 be proc source_to_hir with create_src
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "CREATE: frontend produced HIR1", create_hir1
    proc check_create with results, "CREATE HIR1 content", create_hir1

    Let create_sql be proc generate_sql_from_hir from SqlBackend with create_hir1
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "CREATE: backend produced SQL text", create_sql
    Let create_sql_len be proc string_length from StringCore with create_sql
    proc assert_greater_than from TestUtils with results, "CREATE: emitted SQL non-empty", create_sql_len, 0

    Let create_hir2 be proc source_to_hir with create_sql
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "CREATE: re-parse produced HIR2", create_hir2
    proc check_create with results, "CREATE HIR2 round-trip content", create_hir2

    Note: ---------------------------------------------------------------------
    Note: INSERT with explicit columns + VALUES
    Note: ---------------------------------------------------------------------
    Let insert_src be "INSERT INTO accounts (id, name) VALUES (1, 'Alice')"

    Let insert_hir1 be proc source_to_hir with insert_src
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "INSERT: frontend produced HIR1", insert_hir1
    proc check_insert with results, "INSERT HIR1 content", insert_hir1

    Let insert_sql be proc generate_sql_from_hir from SqlBackend with insert_hir1
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "INSERT: backend produced SQL text", insert_sql
    Let insert_sql_len be proc string_length from StringCore with insert_sql
    proc assert_greater_than from TestUtils with results, "INSERT: emitted SQL non-empty", insert_sql_len, 0

    Let insert_hir2 be proc source_to_hir with insert_sql
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "INSERT: re-parse produced HIR2", insert_hir2
    proc check_insert with results, "INSERT HIR2 round-trip content", insert_hir2

    proc print_summary from TestUtils with results
    Let failed be proc get_failed from TestUtils with results
    proc destroy_test_results from TestUtils with results

    Return failed
End Process
